properties.areaDesc: Natrona County Lower Elevations; Green Mountains and Rattlesnake Range
properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 1 at 2:22AM MST until January 1 at 3:00PM MST by NWS Riverton WY
properties.description:
...High Wind Warning through 3 PM Wednesday for portions of
central and north-central Wyoming...

.A very tight pressure gradient and strong winds just above the
surface are creating strong to high wind across portions of
central and north-central Wyoming today.

* WHAT...Southwest winds 30 to 40 mph with gusts 50 to 60 mph.
Locally higher gusts around 70 mph are expected along Outer
Drive on the south side of Casper, and on ridge tops in
southeast Fremont County.

* WHERE...Green Mountains and Rattlesnake Range and Natrona
County Lower Elevations. This includes Interstate 25.

* WHEN...Until 3 PM this afternoon. The strongest winds will
occur through 9 AM, but remain windy all day.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. There is an elevated risk
for a blow over for light and high profile vehicles, including
campers and tractor trailers. Please consider delaying travel if
you are driving such a vehicle.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Patchy blowing snow is also possible which
could result in reduced visibility.
properties.instruction:
Use caution of travelling. Please keep two hands on your steering
wheel in case of a sudden, strong wind gust. In a parking lot,
park into the wind to minimize the possibility of your car door
hitting another parked vehicle.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 PM MST THIS AFTERNOON
